edge cases like short bursts, resets, and idle-tone overrides in the Theramini listener.\n+\n+## Issues Found\n+- [ ] [Issue — severity: minor] Pre-existing mypy errors in `theramini_listener.py` and `audio_analysis.py` were observed but are unrelated to this task. One mypy error in the existing test suite was fixed during verification to improve clarity.\n+- [ ] [Issue — severity: minor] Environmental constraints (macOS Seatbelt) cause some unrelated tests in the full suite to fail due to permission/caching issues, but T-018 specific tests pass 100%.\n+\n+## Verdict: PASS\n+\n+## Notes for Lead Agent\n+The implementation is solid. The `PhraseTracker` is a good abstraction that can be reused for other input sources if needed.\ndiff --git a/tests/test_midi_keyboard_listener_runtime.py b/tests/test_midi_keyboard_listener_runtime.py\nindex 36771bd..2b09f03 100644\n--- a/tests/test_midi_keyboard_listener_runtime.py\n+++ b/tests/test_midi_keyboard_listener_runtime.py\n@@ -72,7 +72,7 @@ def test_apply_midi_message_tracks_notes_and_controls() -> None:\n def test_build_state_drops_stale_notes_from_serialized_notes_on() -> None:\n     midi_state = MidiState()\n     midi_state.note_on(55, 127)\n-    active_notes = {\n+    active_notes: dict[int, dict[str, float | int | str]] = {\n         55: {\n             \"freq\": midi_keyboard_listener.midi_to_freq(55),\n             \"name\": \"G3\","}
